The various measures of national saving and investment are ways to measure changes in total wealth.
Note: Measured in 1990 international dollars. In order of increasing comprehensiveness, these
measures include: Net investment = net fixed produced capital formation and overseas investment;
Green investment = Net investment + change in natural capital; Genuine savings = Green
investment + education expenditure; GSTFP = Genuine savings + Net present value of total factor
